          <div class="p-8 space-y-6">
            <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Use Meaningful Node IDs
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Name nodes descriptively (e.g., <code class="text-emerald-400">dc1-node1</code>) for easier debugging and monitoring.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Separate Data Directories
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Each node must have its own unique data directory to avoid corruption.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Monitor Replication Lag
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Regularly check cluster status API to ensure peers are synced with low lag.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Open Replication Ports
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Ensure firewall rules allow traffic on replication ports between all nodes.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Odd Number of Nodes
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">For better availability, consider 3 or 5 nodes to handle failures gracefully.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="bg-gray-800/30 rounded-xl p-5 border border-white/5">
                <h3 class="text-white font-bold mb-2 flex items-center">
                  <span class="text-emerald-400 mr-2">✓</span>
                  Low Latency Network
                </h3>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">Place nodes on networks with low latency for faster replication sync.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

